[{"id":"VR857494","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a right triangle labeled Original Prism. A beam of light originating from the left of the figure, enters the left side of the prism at a right angle. The beam travels through the prism and exits from hypotenuse side. The beam is then redirected down and to the right. A perpendicular dashed line to the hypotenuse surface is shown at the point where the ray exists the prism. The bottom right angle below where the ray exits the prism is labeled n sub O. A note indicates the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR857494.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A prism in the shape of a right triangle is made from a transparent material with an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub o\"><math alttext=\"n sub o\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi></msub></math></span></span>, as shown in the figure. A beam of light is normally incident on the left side of the prism, passes through the prism, and is finally refracted as it emerges from the right side of the prism back into the air.</p><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The scenario is repeated with two other prisms, both identical in shape to the original prism but made from materials with different indexes of refraction. Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> is made from a material with an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub X is less than n sub O\"><math alttext=\"n sub X is less than n sub O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub></mstyle></math></span></span>, and Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> is made from a material with an index of refraction <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub Y is greater than n sub O\"><math alttext=\"n sub Y is greater than n sub O\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub></math></span></span>. Which of the following claims about the beam of light is true?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR857494_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The beam follows the same path for prisms <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> that is does for the original prism.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The beam emerges from Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, n sub X is less than n sub O, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, n sub X is less than n sub O, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mstyle></math></span></span> at an angle farther from the normal than it does from Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The beamâ€™s light travels faster after emerging from Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, n sub X is less than n sub O, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, n sub X is less than n sub O, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>X</mtext></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mstyle></math></span></span> than it does after emerging from Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mstyle></math></span></span>.</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The beam cannot undergo total internal reflection in Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"X\"><math alttext=\"X\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">X</mi></math></span></span> , but it might undergo total internal reflection in Prism <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"Y\"><math alttext=\"Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Y</mi></math></span></span> <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\"><math alttext=\"open parenthesis, n sub Y is greater than n sub O, close parenthesis\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle displaystyle=\"true\"><mo>(</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub><mo>&gt;</mo><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>O</mtext></msub><mo>)</mo></mstyle></math></span></span> if <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"n sub Y\"><math alttext=\"n sub Y\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>n</mi><mtext>Y</mtext></msub></math></span></span> is sufficiently large.</p>"],"answer":3}]